metadata.name: Vintage Roll Wallpaper Generator #67
metadata.description:
2048x2048px Generative Image. Vanilla JS

Each pattern in the Vintage Roll Wallpaper Generator is generated by an algorithm which can combine both random and parametric equations creating beautiful and unique forms.
A large screen is recommended to really appreciate details. 

Features


Palette: From several hundreds.
Displacement: The displacement between paper strips (may be none)
NumberOfColors: The colors from the palette used in the pattern (1 to 4)
RollWidth: The width of the paper roll, between 256 and 512
Step: The lenght of the lines in the algorithm
Depth: Number of loops in parametric formulas
Symmetrical: The pattern often is symmetrical, but sometimes is not
Mode: Can be Parametrical, Random or (mostly) both.

There are other internal features which changes with the hash.

Controls

S or double tap - Downloads current image in .png format

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #42
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden “template” canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden ‘template’ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Off the grid V.2 #217
metadata.description:
Vanilla JS + SVG
January 2022

Edition of 512

"Off the grid" is my attempt to bring human imperfection to the strict formality of a generative grid-based piece.

Grid-plotted geometric forms are very slightly offset, rotated out of position by a degree or two, or absented entirely from the grid. The number of passes is dictated by the hash, and the results will vary from minimal (4 passes) to maximal (13 passes). The sizes of the forms can vary or be all the same, leading to quite different outputs, further emphasized by the different 'canvas' sizes.

The features are:
Format (Portrait, Landscape or Square), Palette (10 in total), Coverage (Full or Indented), Passes (the number of times the algorithm makes a grid) and Sizes (the sizes of the shapes in the grid, Single [one size] or Multiple).

'S' saves an SVG
'P' saves a PNG

[Please note this project will display, but will not work as intended on most IOS devices]

metadata.name: GE-I #466
metadata.description:

metadata.name: Haemo Globs #260
metadata.description:
The shape and function of haematids (red blood cells) has always fascinated me. Perhaps their mathematical smoothness and candy-like aspect resonated with me as a child. Their simple appearance distinguished them from the other cell types I had learned about. I imagined them engorged with sweet-flavoured oxygen and juicily popping under my bite.

I hope for this generative artwork to communicate my appreciation for these never-ending body travellers.

metadata.name: Skewed Impression #1
metadata.description:
Skewed concrete poetry
Moire affected typography created by laying 2 or 3 grids of characters on top of each other
Features one of thirteen possible characters
3 grids (75%) or rare 2 grids (25%)
4 possible text colors for each grid
6 possible paper colors including rare blue, green, and dark parchment (10% chance each)
3 styles of paper grain
Differing line gaps and angle of skew for grids 2 and 3
You can save output by pressing s
Uses p5.js and scribble.js
@p1x3lboy June 2022
